{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 JKK_XYPad\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Effortless macro control for REAPER sound designers.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \u51200 ?\u45716 ? \u44172 ?\u51076 ? \u49324 ?\u50868 ?\u46300 ? \u46356 ?\u51088 ?\u51060 ?\u45320 ? \u44608 ?\u51456 ?\u44592 ?(Junki Kim)\u51077 ?\u45768 ?\u45796 ?. \u51060 ? \u49828 ?\u53356 ?\u47549 ?\u53944 ?\u45716 ? REAPER \u51204 ?\u50857 ? \u47588 ?\u53356 ?\u47196 ? \u47588 ?\u54609 ? XY \u54056 ?\u46300 ? \u53812 ?\u51077 ?\u45768 ?\u45796 ?. \u51200 ?\u45716 ? \u51204 ?\u47928 ? \u54532 ?\u47196 ?\u44536 ?\u47000 ?\u47672 ?\u44032 ? \u50500 ?\u45768 ?\u44592 ? \u46412 ?\u47928 ?\u50640 ? \u50724 ?\u47448 ?\u50752 ? \u48260 ?\u44536 ?\u51032 ? \u49688 ?\u51221 ?\u50640 ? \u54869 ?\u49888 ?\u51012 ? \u46300 ?\u47540 ? \u49692 ? \u50630 ?\u49845 ?\u45768 ?\u45796 ?... \u44536 ?\u47000 ?\u46020 ? \u54841 ?\u50668 ? \u44060 ?\u49440 ?\u49324 ?\u54637 ?\u51060 ? \u51080 ?\u45796 ?\u47732 ? \u50616 ?\u51228 ?\u46304 ?\u51648 ? \u51200 ?\u50640 ?\u44172 ? \u47700 ?\u51068 ?\u51012 ? \u48372 ?\u45236 ?\u51452 ?\u49464 ?\u50836 ?!\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 I am {\b Junki Kim}, a game sound designer. JKK_XYPad is a dynamic, intuitive XY pad script designed for REAPER users and sound designers. It lets you link multiple macros to the X and Y axes, allowing you to control and blend parameters simultaneously with fluid, organic mouse movements. As I am not a professional programmer, I may not be perfect at fixing every error or bug, but I am always open to feedback! If you have any suggestions or improvements, please feel free to email me.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Contact: junkikim.sound@gmail.com\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u9881 ?\u65039 ? 1. Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ReaImGui must be installed to use JKK_Visualizer.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li720 \fi0 ReaImGui is an essential library that allows for modern user interfaces within REAPER. Since this script's UI is entirely built on ReaImGui, it is a required component.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Install {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
} The easiest and safest way to install ReaImGui is through {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\b ReaPack}
}}}
. Please refer to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
the ReaPack websit
}}}
 for the installation guide. Once installed, you will see an {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack} menu in REAPER's top menu bar.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Install ReaImGui}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Navigate to {\b Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Browse Packages}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Search for {\f1 ReaImGui}. (If it doesn't appear, follow the guide at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/cfillion/reaimgui"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
{\b this site}
}}}
)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Right-click the {\b ReaImGui / Extensions} package and select {\b Install}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Click {\b Apply} in the bottom right corner.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Restart REAPER after the installation is complete.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Verify ReaImGui Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open REAPER\u8217's Action List (Shortcut: {\f1 ?}).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Search for {\f1 ImGui}. If you see a script named {\b ReaImGui: Demo.lua}, the installation was successful.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Import JKK_XYPad Repository\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Go to Extensions \u8594 ? ReaPack \u8594 ? Manage repositories.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Select Import/export... \u8594 ? Import repositories.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Enter the following URL and click OK:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li1440 \fi0 {\f1 https://github.com/junkikim-sound/JKK_XYPad/raw/master/index.xml}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Find {\b JKK_XYPad} in the package list, right-click to {\b install}, and click {\b Apply}. \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab You can now find and run JKK_XYPad and JKK_Visualizer Editor in your Actions. \sa180\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55357 ?\u56960 ? 2. Introduction\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\cf1 [image: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/908ef485-3651-493e-9ec7-62b69f6dda90]\cf0} JKK_XYPad is a dynamic, intuitive XY pad script designed for REAPER users and sound designers. It lets you link multiple macros to the X and Y axes, allowing you to control and blend parameters simultaneously with fluid, organic mouse movements.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Key Features\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flexible Macro Mapping: Assign any parameter. such as volume, panning, or effect intensity\u8212-to the X and Y axes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Lag & Tracking Control: Adjust how tightly or loosely the "yellow dot" trails behind your mouse pointer. Perfect for creating smooth control.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Orbit Mode: Make the yellow dot rotate automatically. You can customize the size, speed, and shape of its orbit to generate unique tremolo and modulation effects.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Adjustable Peak Positions: Change where the maximum value of each axis is located. (e.g., Maximum values in the center, minimum values on the outer edges).\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Technical Details\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Language: Lua\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Library: REAPER v7.0+ / Dear ImGui\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Optimization: Optimized for low CPU usage even at a smooth 60FPS\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55357 ?\u56529 ? 3. Update Log\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 v1.0.0 (May 23, 2026): Initial Update\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 \u55356 ?\u57098 ? About the Author\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Junki Kim Game Sound Designer Specializing in game audio implementation\par}
}
